The mother of twin boys, born joined at the abdomen, has described her joy after a nine-hour operation successfully separated them.

'It's the most wonderful feeling in the world,' Jenni Ezell told Good Morning America today.

Her six-week-old sons, Owen and Emmett, are now recovering in their own beds in intensive care at Medical City Children's Hospital in Dallas, Texas.

