The couple were told the were expecting conjoined twins in March, and had been advised by one doctor to have an abortion, according to CBS 11.

'We didn’t think that they had a chance. We thought they were not going to make it at all. So we decided to abort,' Mrs Ezell said. 'It was the hardest decision that a mother has to make about her babies.'

However, a specialist at Medical City Dallas renewed their faith, telling them 'These boys have a really good chance. This is not your only option.'

Although they can't hold their babies yet, the Ezells are finally able to start planning their futures.

'Taking them home and having Christmas with them - I’m already planning their first birthday parties,. I'm looking forward to everything,' Mrs Ezell said.

